            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text based upon photograph, after Korhonen</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>(tomb) of Gaius Pompeius Felix and Scribonia Restituta</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Given that both names reflect senatorial families attested in the area, this is assumed to be a freedman and freedwoman of the families. Korhonen notes the absence of 'Dis Manibus' as encouraging a first-century date, alongside the palaeography. Castelli and Ferrara report the right fragment only as a separate text, in addition to reporting the entire text, following a notice in Amico.</p>
            </div>
